obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12833)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12833&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1)This Act may be called the National Commission for`
  line `Women Act, 1990.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `asthe Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
  line
  line `2. 31st January, 1992, vide notification No. S.O. 99(E), dated 31st January, 1992, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec.`
  line `3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12834)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12834&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Commission" means the National Commission for Women constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Member" means a Member of the Commission and includes the Member-Secretary;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12835)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the National Commission for Women.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12835&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `constitute a body to be known as the National Commission for Women to exercise the powers conferred`
  line `on, and to perform the functions assigned to, it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, committed to the cause of women, to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) five Members to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst persons of ability,`
  line `integrity and standing who have had experience in law or legislation, trade unionism, management of`
  line `an industry or organisation committed to increasing the employment potential of women, women's`
  line `voluntary organisations (including women activists), administration, economic development, health,`
  line `education or social welfare:`
  line
  line `Provided that at least one Member each shall be from amongst persons belonging to the`
  line `Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes respectively;`
  line
  line `(c) a Member-Secretary to be nominated by the Central Government, who shall be--`
  line
  line `(i) an expert in the field of management, organisational structure or sociological movement,`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) an officer who is a member of a civil service of the Union or of an all-India service or`
  line `holds a civil post under the Union with appropriate experience.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12836)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12836&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1)The Chairperson`
  line `and every Member shall hold office for such period, not exceeding three years, as may be specified by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or a Member (other than the Member-Secretary who is a member of a civil`
  line `service of the Union or of an all-India service or holds a civil post under the Union) may, by writing and`
  line `addressed to the Central Government, resign from the office of Chairperson or, as the case may be, of the`
  line `Member at any time.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall remove a person from the office of Chairperson or a Member`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2) if that person--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) gets convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government involves moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(c) becomes of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(d) refuses to act or becomes incapable of acting;`
  line
  line `(e) is, without obtaining leave of absence from the Commission, absent from three consecutive`
  line `meetings of the Commission; or`
  line
  line `(f) in the opinion of the Central Government has so abused the position of Chairperson or`
  line `Member as to render that person's continuance in office detrimental to the public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be removed under this clause until that person has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) A vacancy caused under sub-section (2) or otherwise shall be filled by fresh nomination.`
  line
  line `(5) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12837)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Officers and other employees of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12837&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall provide`
  line `the Commission with such officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `the functions of the Commission under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees appointed for the purpose of the Commission shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12838)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Salaries and allowances to be paid out of grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12838&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances payable to the`
  line `Chairperson and Members and the administrative expenses, including salaries, allowances and pensions`
  line `payable to the officers and other employees referred to in section 5, shall be paid out of the grants referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) of section 11.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12839)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12839&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Commission shall be questioned or shall be invalid on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy`
  line `or defect in the constitution of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12840)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Committees of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12840&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may appoint such committees as may be`
  line `necessary for dealing with such special issues as may be taken up by the Commission from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall have the power to co-opt as members of any committee appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) such number of persons, who are not Members of the Commission, as it may think fit and`
  line `the persons so co-opted shall have the right to attend the meetings of the committee and take part in its`
  line `proceedings but shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(3) The persons so co-opted shall be entitled to receive such allowances for attending the meetings of`
  line `the committee as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12841)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Procedure to be regulated by the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12841&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission or a committee thereof`
  line `shall meet as and when necessary and shall meet at such time and place as the Chairperson may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall regulate its own procedure and the procedure of the committees thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the Member-Secretary or`
  line `any other officer of the Commission duly authorised by the Member-Secretary in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12842)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12842&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall perform all or any of the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) investigate and examine all matters relating to the safeguards provided for women under the`
  line `Constitution and other law;`
  line
  line `(b) present to the Central Government, annually and at such other times as the Commission may`
  line `deem fit, reports upon the working of those safeguards;`
  line
  line `(c) make in such reports recommendations for the effective implementation of those safeguards`
  line `for improving the conditions of women by the Union or any State;`
  line
  line `(d) review, from time to time, the existing provisions of the Constitution and other laws affecting`
  line `women and recommend amendments thereto so as to suggest remedial legislative measures to meet`
  line `any lacunae, inadequacies or shortcomings in such legislations;`
  line
  line `(e) take up the cases of violation of the provisions of the Constitution and of other laws relating to`
  line `women with the appropriate authorities;`
  line
  line `(f) look into complaints and take suomoto notice of matters relating to--`
  line
  line `(i) deprivation of womens rights;`
  line
  line `(ii) non-implementation of laws enacted to provide protection to women and also to achieve`
  line `the objective of equality and development;`
  line
  line `(iii) non-compliance of policy decisions, guidelines or instructions aimed at mitigating`
  line `hardships and ensuring welfare and providing relief to women,`
  line
  line `and take up the issues arising out of such matters with appropriate authorities;`
  line
  line `(g) call for special studies or investigations into specific problems or situations arising out of`
  line `discrimination and atrocities against women and identify the constraints so as to recommend`
  line `strategies for their removal;`
  line
  line `(h) undertake promotional and educational research so as to suggest ways of ensuring due`
  line `representation of women in all spheres and identify factors responsible for impeding their`
  line `advancement, such as, lack of access to housing and basic services, inadequate support services and`
  line `technologies for reducing drudgery and occupational health hazards and for increasing their`
  line productivity;
  line
  line `(i) participate and advise on the planning process of socio-economic development of women;`
  line
  line `(j) evaluate the progress of the development of women under the Union and any State;`
  line
  line `(k) inspect or cause to be inspected a jail, remand home, women's institution or other place of`
  line `custody where women are kept as prisoners or otherwise, and take up with the concerned authorities`
  line `for remedial action, if found necessary;`
  line
  line `(l) fund litigation involving issues affecting a large body of women;`
  line
  line `(m) make periodical reports to the Government on any matter pertaining to women and in`
  line `particular various difficulties under which women toil;`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter which may be referred to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall cause all the reports referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) to`
  line `be laid before each House of Parliament along with a memorandum explaining the action taken or`
  line `proposed to be taken on the recommendations relating to the Union and the reasons for the nonacceptance,`
  line `if any of any of such recommendations.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any such reportor any part thereof relates to any matter with which any State Government`
  line `is concerned, the Commission shall forward a copy of such report or part to such State Government who`
  line `shall cause it to be laid before the Legislature of the State along with a memorandum explaining the`
  line `action taken or proposed to be taken on the recommendations relating to the State and the reasons for the`
  line `non-acceptance, if any, of any of such recommendations.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission shall, while investigating any matter referred to in clause (a) or sub-clause (i) of`
  line `clause (f) ofsub-section (1), have all the powers of a civil court trying a suit and, in particular, in respect`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person from any part of India and examining`
  line `him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses and documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12843)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Grants by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12843&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Commission by way of grants such`
  line `sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing the functions under this Act,`
  line `and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the grants referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12844)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12844&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General at such`
  line `intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit shall be`
  line `payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Commission under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges and the`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of`
  line `the offices of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Commission, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government by the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12845)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12845&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `TheCommission shall prepare, in such form and at such time, for each financial`
  line `year, as may be prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the previous`
  line `financial year and forward a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12846)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Annual report and audit report to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12846&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall`
  line `cause the annual report together with a memorandum of action taken on the recommendations contained`
  line `therein, in so far as they relate to the Central Government, and the reasons for the non-acceptance, if any,`
  line `of any of such recommendations and the audit report to be laid as soon as may be after the reports are`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12847)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Chairperson, Members and Staff of the Commission to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12847&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line TheChairperson,
  line `the Members, officers and other employees of the Commission shall be deemed to be public servants`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12848)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Central Government to consult Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12848&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall consult the`
  line `Commission on all major policy matters affecting women.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12849)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756&sectionId=12849&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00004_199020_1517807322756
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Members under sub-section (5) of section 4 and of officers and other employees`
  line `under sub-section(2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) allowances for attending the meetings of the committee by the co-opted persons under subsection`
  line `(3)of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) other matters under clause (f) of sub-section (4) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which the annual statement of accounts shall be maintained under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in, and the time at, which the annual report shall be prepared under section 13;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
